    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-06T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-06T21:00:00-05:00" n="62"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Gemmell, Nina E./27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-07T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 7, 1930—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. My 22 April 5, 1 p.m.<note n="84" xml:id="d62fn84">Not printed.</note>
                    Telegram received this morning from Changsha by China Inland Mission states that
                    Miss Gemmell has been released.<note n="85" xml:id="d62fn85">She was held from
                        March 23 to April 4. In despatch No. 948, April 12, 1930, the Consul General
                        at Hankow reported to the Legation “that $1,100 in cash was paid to the
                        bandits and that it is believed this payment brought about the release of
                        Miss Gemmell.” (393.1111 Gemmell, Nina E./36)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Legation, Nanking and Shanghai informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
